WEBVTT

00:15.750 --> 00:17.542
♪ ("JETT" THEME PLAYS) ♪

00:18.750 --> 00:19.834
WOMAN: 62,000.

00:20.125 --> 00:21.208
Rent us the house
for the year.

00:21.291 --> 00:22.667
Wonder if you'd come
for a ride with me.

00:22.750 --> 00:23.750
Let me get my purse.

00:25.375 --> 00:28.417
Have we, or have we not,
been getting serious?

00:28.500 --> 00:30.125
Why are you trying
to provoke me?

00:30.208 --> 00:31.834
This is not
what a professional does.

00:31.917 --> 00:33.583
This feels personal.

00:33.667 --> 00:34.750
(GUNSHOTS)

00:35.709 --> 00:38.291
He's a cop.
Detective Dillon.

00:39.166 --> 00:40.250
(GRUNTS)

00:41.166 --> 00:42.875
Junior. Junior...

00:43.083 --> 00:45.083
My name is Charles Ju--

00:45.750 --> 00:47.625
Charlie, I'm sorry.
We gotta go.

00:49.125 --> 00:51.041
Jack Dillon, now come on,
I don't want to shoot you.

00:51.125 --> 00:53.542
-What's your idea?
-Go somewhere and get a drink.

00:53.625 --> 00:54.625
I need you to run
by the house

00:54.709 --> 00:56.208
and grab stuff
for you and Alice.

00:56.500 --> 00:58.458
-Will you be careful?
-Yes.

00:59.041 --> 01:00.291
Call me when you have Alice.

01:00.792 --> 01:03.333
DILLON: You always have to
have a plan, ways in, ways out.

01:03.583 --> 01:05.792
-I'm not supposed to be here.
-(PHONE BUZZES)

01:05.875 --> 01:06.875
Bestic is here?

01:06.959 --> 01:08.083
MILJAN BESTIC: Daisy Kowalski.

01:08.166 --> 01:10.250
Let's meet
somewhere very public.

01:10.333 --> 01:12.125
Breakfast, 9 a.m.

01:12.625 --> 01:14.959
-Sleep tight, Daisy.
-♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:23.625 --> 01:26.792
♪ ♪

01:34.083 --> 01:37.291
(heels clicking, echoing)

02:07.166 --> 02:08.709
(clicks)

02:15.709 --> 02:17.208
-(lighter clicks)
-(elevator dings)

02:18.041 --> 02:21.166
♪ ♪

02:25.208 --> 02:26.375
(clicks)

02:29.291 --> 02:30.417
(unlocks door)

02:30.500 --> 02:32.291
Narrator:
On the platform, the biologist

02:32.375 --> 02:34.625
must take his samples,
and his chances,

02:34.709 --> 02:38.041
among the sharp flensing knives
on the blood-slick deck.

02:38.125 --> 02:40.208
(TV playing indistinctly)

02:41.208 --> 02:45.083
-(muted gunshots)
-(bodies thud)

02:45.166 --> 02:47.000
Narrator (on TV):
Running does not help.

02:47.083 --> 02:49.333
Teeth are a prime target.

02:49.417 --> 02:52.500
More heat lost.

02:52.583 --> 02:56.417
Life is subject to the general
diffusion of all energy.

02:58.792 --> 03:01.208
Concentrated heat was the past.

03:01.291 --> 03:03.542
Diffused heat is the future.

03:05.208 --> 03:09.250
The young lady's heat,
eventually, will be lost
in outer space.

03:18.083 --> 03:21.250
♪ ♪

03:31.792 --> 03:34.000
(woman sighs)

03:37.583 --> 03:40.667
♪ ♪

03:43.166 --> 03:47.083
(woman sighing)

03:55.792 --> 03:57.959
(woman sighing)

04:02.125 --> 04:05.291
(inaudible)

04:21.166 --> 04:23.291
♪ ♪

04:23.375 --> 04:26.834
(woman sighs)

04:33.041 --> 04:36.291
(record crackling, popping)

04:44.125 --> 04:46.500
(mouths)

04:46.583 --> 04:48.583
(record crackling stops)

04:48.667 --> 04:51.834
(wind whooshing)

05:06.542 --> 05:09.500
(distant shrieking)

05:11.041 --> 05:13.917
(wind blowing)

05:23.083 --> 05:24.041
(gunshot)

05:26.792 --> 05:29.500
♪ ♪

05:32.166 --> 05:36.375
♪ ♪

05:43.750 --> 05:47.375
(rapid breathing)

05:51.166 --> 05:52.542
(gasps)

05:54.208 --> 05:55.875
What time is it?

05:55.959 --> 05:57.375
Eight-thirty.

05:57.458 --> 05:59.417
I fell asleep?

06:00.208 --> 06:01.417
(sighs)

06:02.583 --> 06:05.750
♪ ♪

06:31.959 --> 06:33.917
♪ ♪

06:51.750 --> 06:53.834
♪ ♪

07:15.250 --> 07:17.667
(clicking)

07:22.291 --> 07:25.333
♪ ♪

07:33.041 --> 07:35.333
-Ronnie: Ms. Kowalski.
-Jett: Ronnie.

07:42.667 --> 07:45.875
(indistinct chattering)

07:52.000 --> 07:53.875
Follow me, please.

08:13.792 --> 08:16.041
This will be returned
to you after.

08:24.291 --> 08:25.875
(sucks fingers)

08:25.959 --> 08:27.792
I was starving,
so I already started.

08:27.875 --> 08:30.250
Please forgive me.
Do you want to get
yourself a plate?

08:30.834 --> 08:32.792
-No.
-Are you sure?

08:33.625 --> 08:36.083
-Yes.
-You know what they say.

08:36.166 --> 08:39.458
That breakfast is the most
important meal of the day.

08:41.458 --> 08:43.417
You seem a little tense.

08:44.500 --> 08:46.000
There's something
about you that makes me

08:46.083 --> 08:48.500
wanna kick your
fucking face in, but...

08:48.583 --> 08:50.792
-I'm all right.
-(chuckles)

08:53.458 --> 08:55.834
I think that you
are downplaying it.

08:55.917 --> 08:57.458
What you want to do to me?

09:00.375 --> 09:03.041
Dillon:
Lamar Benjamin,
aka Judge.

09:03.125 --> 09:04.875
Nasty piece of work.

09:04.959 --> 09:08.792
Twice deployed in Iraq,
where he had a nervous breakdown
at a raid in Fallujah.

09:08.875 --> 09:10.834
Came home,
beat his girlfriend to death.

09:10.917 --> 09:12.917
A week later,
he killed Jimarcus Hooks,

09:13.000 --> 09:16.333
known dope dealer he believed
was screwing the girlfriend.

09:16.417 --> 09:19.458
At the trial, they brought
in VA psychiatrists to testify,

09:19.542 --> 09:21.625
and they declared Lamar insane.

09:21.709 --> 09:24.875
He spent six months
at a state hospital
in Hawthorne,

09:24.959 --> 09:28.375
has been killing people
ever since he got out.

09:29.083 --> 09:31.417
Jett:
If you know all that,
why can't you arrest him?

09:31.500 --> 09:33.250
Oh, we arrested him.

09:33.333 --> 09:36.041
In seven years of arrests,
convictions,

09:36.125 --> 09:38.417
plea bargains,
and insanity judgments,

09:38.500 --> 09:41.250
Lamar spent a grand total
of 10 months behind bars.

09:41.333 --> 09:43.166
This all before
he started his little...

09:43.250 --> 09:45.166
side business
of killing for hire.

09:45.250 --> 09:48.583
I'd say he's murdered...
at least 20 people.

09:49.083 --> 09:51.583
Tell me about
the hotel manager.

09:51.667 --> 09:53.041
Hmm, a little squirrelly,

09:53.125 --> 09:55.750
-but he's been okay, I guess.
-He's a day manager?

09:55.834 --> 09:58.667
Executive
assistant manager.

09:58.750 --> 10:01.417
Parrish is who we dealt with
during our surveillance.

10:01.500 --> 10:03.125
You want him
to set up your guy?

10:03.208 --> 10:05.625
I'm not asking
for your permission.

10:06.542 --> 10:08.750
You're taking a lot
of chances walking in there.

10:08.834 --> 10:11.375
I don't have a lot of options.

10:12.333 --> 10:14.125
Can you get a hold of Parrish?

10:15.250 --> 10:17.500
He doesn't need
to know any details.

10:18.667 --> 10:20.750
Guy could be sleeping, you know?

10:20.834 --> 10:23.166
Jett:
He'll no doubt be
surprised to see us.

10:24.000 --> 10:25.458
(whispering):
Walter!

10:25.834 --> 10:27.208
Honey!

10:28.125 --> 10:29.000
Walter!

10:29.083 --> 10:30.709
-What's wrong?
-Shh!

10:30.792 --> 10:33.041
I think somebody's
in the house.

10:34.041 --> 10:35.208
(sighs)

10:37.250 --> 10:38.875
Don't fall
asleep on me.

10:38.959 --> 10:40.667
All right.
I'm awake.

10:40.750 --> 10:42.667
-I'm awake.
-Did you not set the alarm?

10:42.750 --> 10:44.792
-Of course I did.
-You forgot again.

10:44.875 --> 10:48.417
-No, I didn't.
-Then how come it didn't go off?

10:50.417 --> 10:53.625
-(sighs) Fuck.
-What are you doing?

10:53.709 --> 10:56.667
-Walter: I'm gonna go
see downstairs.
-We should call 911.

10:56.750 --> 10:58.125
Whoa, whoa. Don't get
ahead of yourself.

10:58.208 --> 11:01.166
Let me check it out.
If you hear me raise
my voice,

11:01.250 --> 11:03.041
then call the cops.

11:03.125 --> 11:04.375
(laughs)
That's stupid.

11:04.458 --> 11:05.417
(light clicks)

11:06.166 --> 11:07.583
-Try to stay calm.
-Jesus Christ!

11:07.667 --> 11:09.667
-Who the fuck are you?
-It's a home invasion!

11:09.750 --> 11:12.709
Annie, Walter,
keep your voices down.

11:12.792 --> 11:15.083
This is not
a home invasion.

11:15.166 --> 11:17.125
What... What
do you want?

11:17.208 --> 11:20.000
My associate, Detective Dillon,
is downstairs.

11:20.083 --> 11:21.583
He would like a word
with you, Walter.

11:21.667 --> 11:25.083
-Why?
-No, no, I know
a Detective Dillon.

11:25.166 --> 11:26.709
What is this about?

11:26.792 --> 11:28.583
Come downstairs
and we'll explain.

11:28.667 --> 11:30.542
I would've had him
come up, but...

11:30.625 --> 11:32.959
his face is covered
in stitches.

11:33.041 --> 11:34.750
It's a little
distracting.

11:35.625 --> 11:37.542
And for
the record,

11:37.625 --> 11:40.542
Walter did not forget
to set the alarm tonight.

11:41.250 --> 11:43.333
Let me tell you a story.

11:43.417 --> 11:45.500
After the story,
if you still feel like

11:45.583 --> 11:48.333
kicking my face in, or worse,

11:48.417 --> 11:52.208
well, then, at least
you have the information
you need to move forward.

11:52.291 --> 11:53.500
Please, sit down.

11:59.375 --> 12:02.667
Once upon a time,
there was a beautiful woman,

12:02.750 --> 12:04.542
not your garden-variety
beautiful.

12:04.625 --> 12:07.917
This woman was
dramatically attractive.

12:09.959 --> 12:13.166
She had perfect skin, and...

12:14.458 --> 12:17.625
full lips, and when she smiled,

12:19.291 --> 12:21.959
it could melt an iceberg.

12:23.250 --> 12:25.458
And her name was Cristelle.

12:26.625 --> 12:29.291
And I was so in love with her.

12:30.125 --> 12:31.667
And she loved me, too.

12:31.750 --> 12:33.834
I believe that.

12:35.250 --> 12:39.333
The problem was
that she was pregnant
with another man's child.

12:39.959 --> 12:43.166
This man,
he was a dangerous man.

12:43.917 --> 12:46.125
He was a real gangster.

12:47.875 --> 12:50.291
He's Charlie Baudelaire.

12:51.250 --> 12:52.792
And Charlie,

12:52.875 --> 12:55.667
well, he did not take
kindly to her telling him

12:55.750 --> 12:57.208
that she had feelings
for another man

12:57.291 --> 13:00.542
while she was carrying
his child in her womb.

13:02.959 --> 13:05.166
Well, Charlie yelled at her,

13:06.000 --> 13:09.291
and he beat her,
and he called her a whore.

13:11.667 --> 13:14.417
In retrospect,
I believe we severely

13:14.500 --> 13:17.333
underestimated
her power over us.

13:17.834 --> 13:21.166
We thought we were tussling
over a fashion model.

13:21.959 --> 13:24.583
Two young men marking
their territory.

13:26.291 --> 13:27.834
But I digress.

13:30.625 --> 13:32.625
Charlie:
Sherman Grant Quinn.

13:32.709 --> 13:33.875
-No, no, Chin.
-(door opens)

13:33.959 --> 13:36.667
-Why won't you come in?
-Because I'm busy.

13:36.750 --> 13:39.125
-Go to bed, Vivian.
-Answer me this one thing,

13:39.208 --> 13:40.834
but tell me
the truth this time.

13:40.917 --> 13:42.417
-I always tell the truth.
-(scoffs)

13:42.500 --> 13:44.000
-Like fuck you do.
-Oh, you see?

13:44.083 --> 13:46.041
Yeah, well, I don't care
for that kind of language.

13:46.125 --> 13:48.208
I don't give a shit what kind
of language you care for.

13:48.291 --> 13:51.750
If I gave a shit, I wouldn't
be talking at all, would I?

13:51.834 --> 13:55.250
-You know, you're
not making any sense.
-I'm making all the sense.

13:55.917 --> 13:58.000
(sighs) Yeah, maybe you
shouldn't drink so much.

13:58.083 --> 13:59.834
Just because you are
in your own world

13:59.917 --> 14:04.041
and don't make
an effort to understand
jack shit of what I'm...

14:06.375 --> 14:08.417
How many times do you come
to this fuck pad a month?

14:08.500 --> 14:10.750
-Good night, Vivian.
-Bennie, you understand--

14:10.834 --> 14:12.583
Look, leave Bennie out of this!

14:13.625 --> 14:15.959
Go get undressed
and get in bed!

14:16.041 --> 14:17.625
Oh, ho, ho.

14:17.709 --> 14:19.208
Now, it comes out.

14:19.291 --> 14:20.834
Are we a little
horny maybe?

14:20.917 --> 14:23.041
We're done here.
Good night.

14:23.125 --> 14:24.458
(phone ringing)

14:24.542 --> 14:26.959
Charlie says we're done.
Oh, okay, Charlie.

14:27.041 --> 14:29.083
Whatever you say.
Charlie knows best.

14:29.166 --> 14:31.667
No, sir! Yes, sir!
Charlie, sir!

14:31.750 --> 14:33.458
Get her in bed
before I smack her.

14:33.542 --> 14:36.375
-Mrs. Baudelaire.
-What ever happened
to keep Bennie out of this?

14:36.458 --> 14:38.583
Why can't you just tuck me in?

14:38.667 --> 14:40.667
Good night! (sighs)

14:43.000 --> 14:45.208
-Yes.
-Bestic (over phone): Charlie?

14:45.291 --> 14:46.959
Miljan Bestic.

14:47.792 --> 14:49.208
How'd you get this number?

14:49.291 --> 14:51.125
I heard about your son.

14:51.208 --> 14:54.083
Nothing I can say
will make that better.

14:54.166 --> 14:56.291
But I have
a proposition for you.

14:57.417 --> 14:59.291
More like a gift.

14:59.375 --> 15:00.542
(sighs)

15:00.625 --> 15:02.750
Vivian:
Why doesn't
he want to tuck me in?

15:02.834 --> 15:04.750
Doesn't even want to touch me,
he's so tired out

15:04.834 --> 15:07.041
from all of his
skanky whores.

15:07.417 --> 15:09.250
He has no need for this.

15:11.208 --> 15:12.917
-Vivian...
-(sniffles)

15:13.959 --> 15:16.500
His son was murdered today.

15:19.834 --> 15:22.250
Do you know
I almost got murdered, too?

15:22.333 --> 15:24.333
You told me, yes.

15:24.667 --> 15:26.834
He was so close.

15:27.458 --> 15:30.000
I almost peed in my pants.

15:30.667 --> 15:32.000
(sniffles)

15:34.333 --> 15:37.959
-I'm gonna go now.
-Help me with this first.

15:38.834 --> 15:40.000
Please?

15:45.583 --> 15:46.959
(sighs)

15:51.250 --> 15:52.583
She's gonna be fine.

15:52.667 --> 15:54.875
-(Vivian whimpers)
-(glass shatters)

15:55.500 --> 15:56.834
(sighs)

15:57.667 --> 16:00.083
Who else do you
want me to try?

16:06.750 --> 16:08.417
That's it for tonight.

16:12.542 --> 16:13.667
(sighs)

16:15.750 --> 16:17.458
When the baby was born,

16:17.542 --> 16:20.834
Charlie sent some men
to steal it from her...

16:21.875 --> 16:24.500
because he knew that if it
was raised under her hand,

16:24.583 --> 16:27.291
the child would grow
to hate his father,

16:27.375 --> 16:28.750
and he would not
have a proper heir

16:28.834 --> 16:31.041
for the business
he was building.

16:31.583 --> 16:34.458
So, Charlie brought Junior here,

16:34.542 --> 16:36.709
and he raised him in the States.

16:38.709 --> 16:41.166
And I dated this woman...

16:42.083 --> 16:45.375
in the aftermath
of this awful tragedy.

16:48.709 --> 16:52.458
A mother having her
child stolen from her.

16:52.959 --> 16:54.583
Can you imagine that?

16:57.083 --> 16:58.458
Of course you can.

17:10.750 --> 17:13.250
♪ ♪

18:04.792 --> 18:07.959
♪ ♪

18:15.208 --> 18:16.917
Bestic:
Many years later,

18:17.000 --> 18:18.583
I learned that Junior
was in Marseilles,

18:18.667 --> 18:21.041
doing business
in his father's name.

18:21.125 --> 18:23.333
He is buying
weapons from this...

18:24.125 --> 18:27.500
particularly nasty arms dealer
that I know.

18:28.542 --> 18:31.041
So, I insert myself
into this evening.

18:33.458 --> 18:35.458
And I watch him,

18:36.375 --> 18:38.375
and I talk to him.

18:39.458 --> 18:41.125
It's Junior.

18:44.792 --> 18:47.125
His eyes reminded me so much

18:47.208 --> 18:49.917
of my dearly departed Cristelle.

18:50.000 --> 18:51.583
Her death was no accident.

18:51.667 --> 18:54.875
Charlie was behind it,
bet you didn't know that.

18:57.583 --> 18:58.917
(chuckles)

19:00.667 --> 19:02.208
Am I boring you?

19:06.208 --> 19:07.875
So, I am boring you.

19:08.208 --> 19:09.750
Only a little.

19:11.375 --> 19:13.000
Well, that evening in Marseilles

19:13.083 --> 19:16.041
was one of degenerate
debauchery.

19:17.000 --> 19:18.917
There were drugs,

19:19.000 --> 19:21.709
fucking, beatings,
what have you.

19:22.542 --> 19:24.458
And I make sure that Junior

19:24.542 --> 19:28.291
is roasted and toasted
beyond fucking imagination...

19:30.709 --> 19:33.375
so that when he wakes
up in the morning

19:33.458 --> 19:36.542
with three underage
male prostitutes

19:36.625 --> 19:38.792
chopped in pieces,

19:39.917 --> 19:41.583
well,

19:41.667 --> 19:43.875
he's beside himself.

19:45.625 --> 19:47.417
And I help him.

19:47.500 --> 19:49.709
And I counseled him.

19:51.667 --> 19:53.250
I clean up his mess.

19:53.750 --> 19:56.166
-Do you follow
what I am saying?
-Yes.

19:56.250 --> 19:58.250
I don't think that you do.

19:59.250 --> 20:01.667
No matter how Charlie
tried to raise his child

20:01.750 --> 20:03.625
to do as he was told,

20:03.709 --> 20:05.333
Junior grew up spiteful.

20:05.417 --> 20:08.750
A snake snapping at its
own tail, so you used that.

20:10.625 --> 20:14.125
You can imagine the level
of gratitude he feels for me.

20:14.667 --> 20:17.041
You can imagine
the immense debt he owes me,

20:17.125 --> 20:20.291
knowing that I have pictures
of his misadventures.

20:20.834 --> 20:23.750
Pictures that, at any moment,
I could give to the task force

20:23.834 --> 20:26.333
that is investigating
the Baudelaires.

20:28.000 --> 20:30.583
You know some of those
detectives, I believe.

20:31.375 --> 20:33.333
Whatever you think you're doing,

20:33.417 --> 20:36.959
whatever provocation you
believe will catch me off guard,

20:38.291 --> 20:40.083
I'm not interested.

20:40.166 --> 20:41.792
I came here to tell you,

20:41.875 --> 20:44.834
I will not do what
you ask me to do.

20:44.917 --> 20:46.792
I won't do anything
more for you.

20:47.959 --> 20:51.000
I assume you came
in the hopes of killing me.

20:51.542 --> 20:54.417
But killing me will not solve
your problem with Charlie,

20:54.500 --> 20:57.375
so why don't you just
kill him instead,

20:57.458 --> 20:58.834
and settle
our account?

20:58.917 --> 21:01.083
Charlie and I will work out
our differences without you.

21:01.166 --> 21:03.375
You can't honestly
believe that.

21:04.500 --> 21:06.667
We're done, you and I.

21:07.667 --> 21:08.834
We are not done.

21:08.917 --> 21:10.834
We are done.

21:13.208 --> 21:14.250
(door opens)

21:14.333 --> 21:15.834
Bestic:
Perfect timing.

21:20.500 --> 21:22.500
Charlie.

21:25.333 --> 21:27.500
(neon sign buzzing)

21:32.208 --> 21:35.375
-(sultry music playing)
-Woman (on video): Yeah! Yeah!

21:35.458 --> 21:36.792
-(slapping)
-(moaning)

21:36.875 --> 21:40.125
Woman:
Oh yeah! Fuck me, fuck me,
fuck me harder!

21:40.208 --> 21:43.917
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
harder, harder!

21:44.000 --> 21:45.709
Lamar:
This is the cat.

21:53.542 --> 21:55.041
When was this?

22:03.750 --> 22:05.125
Two months back, maybe.

22:05.208 --> 22:07.458
Cops still have
no idea how it was done.

