39:12.583 --> 39:16.250
You're... you're my
best friend, Eddie.

39:19.208 --> 39:21.583
♪ When I come around ♪

39:21.667 --> 39:23.500
Never known Kowalski
to put something together

39:23.583 --> 39:25.000
this last minute,

39:25.083 --> 39:27.375
so something major
must be going down.

39:28.208 --> 39:30.750
There's a decoy
already in place.

39:30.834 --> 39:32.375
She wants you
to take the kill-shot.

39:33.333 --> 39:34.583
Copy that.

39:39.250 --> 39:42.333
♪ ♪

39:50.709 --> 39:52.333
This man's
simplicity

39:52.417 --> 39:55.125
was overwhelming
towards the end.

39:56.250 --> 39:59.333
It's not your fault, Bennie,
so don't make it personal.

40:00.417 --> 40:03.250
There are a lot of guys who
could use a man like you.

40:03.709 --> 40:06.125
Now, go on. Get out of here.

40:07.208 --> 40:10.166
This is a one-time offer only.

40:10.250 --> 40:11.417
She's staying.

40:20.667 --> 40:22.333
-(gunshot)
-(grunts)

40:25.208 --> 40:28.166
(gunfire)

40:30.750 --> 40:32.667
(gunfire)

40:34.333 --> 40:36.083
(glass shattering)

40:36.166 --> 40:38.166
-(gunfire)
-(groaning)

40:40.458 --> 40:41.500
(grunts)

40:43.166 --> 40:46.291
♪ ♪

41:07.917 --> 41:10.583
(panting)

41:10.667 --> 41:11.667
(clicks empty)

41:13.041 --> 41:14.250
(panting)

41:14.333 --> 41:16.291
You sent this guy?

41:16.375 --> 41:18.166
I knew you'd try
to pull something.

41:18.250 --> 41:20.750
-(door opens)
-(alarm blaring)

41:22.250 --> 41:25.000
Mr. Bestic, I'm Walter Parrish,
the executive assistant manager.

41:25.083 --> 41:26.583
We need to get you
out of here, sir.

41:26.667 --> 41:28.458
There's another gunman
in the building.

41:28.542 --> 41:30.125
You need to come
with me, please.

41:30.208 --> 41:31.375
What about my wife?

41:34.542 --> 41:36.750
Why... yes, of course,

41:36.834 --> 41:39.250
uh, Mrs. Bestic.

41:39.333 --> 41:41.458
-I'm fine here.
-Sweetheart,
there's another gunman.

41:41.542 --> 41:43.583
You go. I twisted my ankle.

41:44.625 --> 41:46.834
It's better you come.

41:46.917 --> 41:48.250
For Alice's sake.

41:49.792 --> 41:52.417
(alarm blaring)

41:53.125 --> 41:55.125
-What about Alice?
-You'll see.

41:55.208 --> 41:58.291
♪ ♪

42:01.834 --> 42:03.542
You'll be safe in here.

42:05.917 --> 42:07.166
Call your
friend,

42:07.250 --> 42:08.417
Phoenix.

42:09.917 --> 42:11.291
Go on.

42:16.250 --> 42:20.083
-(thunder rumbling)
-(TV playing indistinctly)

42:23.208 --> 42:24.875
Alice:
Phoenix!

42:30.792 --> 42:32.417
No!

42:34.792 --> 42:35.959
Evans: Drive!

42:36.208 --> 42:38.333
(tires screech)

42:45.542 --> 42:48.625
♪ ♪

43:03.625 --> 43:05.792
♪ ♪

43:31.583 --> 43:32.500
(grunts)

43:34.834 --> 43:36.667
Alice, run! Run!

43:37.667 --> 43:38.834
Alice:
Phoenix!

43:38.917 --> 43:40.667
(grunting)

43:43.959 --> 43:45.458
(tires screech)

43:48.542 --> 43:49.709
(shutter snap)

43:54.750 --> 43:56.667
(phone ringing)

43:56.750 --> 43:58.875
(alarm blaring)

44:00.834 --> 44:04.000
(crowd chattering)

44:05.792 --> 44:08.041
-Phoenix (phone): Hello?
-It's me.

44:08.750 --> 44:12.000
-(crying)
-(thunder rumbling)

44:15.125 --> 44:15.959
He took her.

44:16.041 --> 44:17.291
(sobbing)

44:17.375 --> 44:19.500
The guy in Maria's
photos. He took her.

44:20.667 --> 44:22.333
I'm so sorry.

44:26.417 --> 44:29.417
Did you honestly think that
I would walk into a situation

44:29.500 --> 44:31.583
with you without
taking out insurance?

44:33.542 --> 44:34.500
-(gunshot)
-(glass shatters)

44:34.583 --> 44:35.583
(grunt)

44:36.417 --> 44:37.208
Oh God!

44:37.291 --> 44:40.208
(gasping)

44:42.875 --> 44:44.917
(sirens wail)

44:47.333 --> 44:48.792
What are you doing?

44:48.875 --> 44:50.917
-Mr. Parrish.
-(groans)

44:51.375 --> 44:53.083
I'll take it from
here, thank you.

44:53.917 --> 44:54.917
Okay.

44:59.250 --> 45:00.917
Where is she?

45:01.750 --> 45:04.959
If you kill me,
you will never find her.

45:05.917 --> 45:07.125
(screams)

45:07.208 --> 45:08.959
My daughter.

45:10.709 --> 45:12.792
(police radio chatter)

45:12.875 --> 45:15.959
♪ ♪

45:17.542 --> 45:18.709
Time to go.

45:18.792 --> 45:20.458
-My daughter!
-(screaming)

45:21.166 --> 45:22.792
(gasping)

45:25.667 --> 45:28.458
I have nothing
personal against you.

45:29.792 --> 45:32.000
Solonik is cleaning house.

45:34.417 --> 45:36.333
I don't know anymore.

45:36.417 --> 45:38.083
I am middleman.

45:39.291 --> 45:41.291
But don't kid yourself.

45:42.291 --> 45:45.083
The Russians will
skin you alive.

45:47.792 --> 45:49.917
(screams)

45:53.542 --> 45:55.291
Bestic: This is not you.

45:55.375 --> 45:57.041
You are a professional.

45:59.750 --> 46:02.625
None of what you are
doing makes any sense!

46:02.709 --> 46:05.208
You're letting your
feelings take over.

46:09.000 --> 46:11.166
I'm not gonna argue with you.

46:12.083 --> 46:14.291
You are signing your
own death sentence!

46:14.375 --> 46:16.375
You keep saying that.

46:17.250 --> 46:20.041
Viktor Solonik will
never forgive this.

46:20.125 --> 46:22.000
(sirens blare)

46:23.041 --> 46:24.917
He will hunt you
down and kill you.

46:25.000 --> 46:27.041
I'll take my chances.

46:28.667 --> 46:30.041
(inaudible)

46:30.834 --> 46:31.959
-(gunshot)
-(bullet thuds)

46:32.041 --> 46:35.333
-(alarm blaring)
-(indistinct chatter)

46:40.458 --> 46:41.750
Man:
Clear the lobby!

46:45.583 --> 46:48.709
(sirens wailing)

46:50.792 --> 46:54.000
(helicopter whirring)

46:58.083 --> 46:59.709
(siren blaring)

47:13.709 --> 47:15.166
Officer 1:
Move it!

47:17.542 --> 47:18.917
Officer 2:
Go!

47:21.917 --> 47:25.083
(siren blaring)

47:28.000 --> 47:31.208
(phone keypad beeping)

47:33.041 --> 47:36.208
(phone buzzing)

47:40.542 --> 47:43.792
-(police radio chatter)
-(helicopter whirring)

47:54.083 --> 47:57.250
(sirens wailing)

48:01.709 --> 48:02.959
(tires screech)

48:03.041 --> 48:06.125
♪ ♪

48:12.417 --> 48:15.125
Fred said things
got a bit confusing.

48:15.792 --> 48:17.166
He get out?

48:17.500 --> 48:18.917
He's out.

48:21.333 --> 48:24.000
(rapid breathing)

48:32.041 --> 48:32.959
(gasps)

48:34.000 --> 48:35.709
What time is it?

48:35.792 --> 48:37.000
Eight-thirty.

48:37.083 --> 48:38.917
(sighs) I fell asleep?

48:43.000 --> 48:44.625
What were you
dreaming about?

48:45.417 --> 48:46.500
What?

48:46.959 --> 48:49.500
You were making little
sounds in your sleep.

48:50.208 --> 48:52.250
Something was
upsetting you.

48:52.875 --> 48:54.208
That's what you
wanna talk about,

48:54.291 --> 48:55.709
what I was
dreaming?

48:57.000 --> 48:58.709
What do you
wanna talk about?

48:59.583 --> 49:00.500
(sighs)

49:02.959 --> 49:05.041
I don't remember any
of my dreams since...

49:05.125 --> 49:06.917
I was 9 or 10.

49:07.000 --> 49:09.208
Back then, I always
dreamed of baseball.

49:10.166 --> 49:12.959
Are we really having
this conversation?

49:13.500 --> 49:14.834
I'll call you
when it's done.

49:14.917 --> 49:16.834
I'm not sure
I'll be here.

49:17.291 --> 49:19.417
(sighs) I wouldn't go out
wandering, I were you.

49:19.500 --> 49:21.500
It's not
that simple.

49:24.333 --> 49:25.709
It never is.

49:29.667 --> 49:31.333
Good luck today.

49:46.166 --> 49:46.959
(sighs)

49:47.041 --> 49:50.166
♪ ♪

50:06.208 --> 50:08.417
(distant siren wails)

50:33.000 --> 50:35.125
(clock ticking)

50:50.291 --> 50:51.417
(sighs)

50:58.709 --> 51:00.083
(sighs)

51:01.959 --> 51:03.667
How you doing,
partner?

51:04.583 --> 51:05.959
Stop the car.

51:07.500 --> 51:10.041
(heavy breathing)

51:10.125 --> 51:11.083
(groans)

51:14.333 --> 51:16.458
(coughing)

51:19.125 --> 51:20.083
(groans)

51:22.917 --> 51:24.000
(sighs)

51:27.333 --> 51:30.458
♪ ♪

51:47.333 --> 51:50.500
(phone buzzing)

52:16.875 --> 52:18.208
(clicks)

52:21.125 --> 52:24.208
(spinning cylinder)

52:28.375 --> 52:29.542
(clicks)

52:32.083 --> 52:34.250
(spinning cylinder)

52:42.166 --> 52:43.333
(clicks)

52:46.291 --> 52:48.542
(spins cylinder)

53:04.041 --> 53:05.625
(sighs)

53:07.667 --> 53:08.750
(sighs)

53:10.667 --> 53:11.667
(clicks)

53:11.750 --> 53:14.875
(crying)

53:17.500 --> 53:20.625
(phone buzzing)

53:22.083 --> 53:25.000
(wind blowing)

53:25.083 --> 53:27.750
(buzzing continues)

53:46.125 --> 53:47.750
Jackie?

53:48.834 --> 53:50.542
What's wrong?

53:50.625 --> 53:51.875
(sobs)

53:51.959 --> 53:54.625
He-- he took Alice.

53:55.834 --> 53:57.166
What?

53:58.291 --> 54:00.333
I fucked up.

54:00.417 --> 54:02.083
Are you okay?

54:03.750 --> 54:05.333
No.

54:06.542 --> 54:08.750
Where are you
right now?

54:10.625 --> 54:12.625
Wait.

54:12.709 --> 54:14.375
There's more.

54:16.959 --> 54:19.583
(sighs) She's yours.

54:19.667 --> 54:21.291
What?

54:22.834 --> 54:24.000
(sobs)

54:24.959 --> 54:27.709
I know I should be telling
you this in person, but...

54:28.500 --> 54:31.333
I got afraid I wouldn't
see you again. (sniffles)

54:33.667 --> 54:35.834
You're her father.

54:36.959 --> 54:39.667
I'm sorry I didn't
tell you before.

54:44.166 --> 54:45.542
(sighs)

54:45.625 --> 54:47.709
I don't know
if she's alive.

54:50.458 --> 54:52.000
I'll help
you find her.

54:52.083 --> 54:55.208
♪ ♪

54:56.208 --> 54:57.375
(sobs)

54:57.458 --> 54:59.583
(wind blowing)

55:04.875 --> 55:06.834
(sighs)

55:42.417 --> 55:44.542
♪ ♪

55:58.417 --> 56:01.542
♪ ♪

56:32.458 --> 56:35.583
♪ ♪

57:02.500 --> 57:05.625
♪ ♪

57:29.500 --> 57:32.625
♪ ♪

57:48.125 --> 57:49.625
You're taking a lot of chances
walking in there.

57:50.041 --> 57:51.583
I don't have a lot of options.

57:51.667 --> 57:53.125
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

57:53.917 --> 57:55.625
There's something about you
that makes me want to kick

57:55.709 --> 57:57.667
-your fucking face.
-(CHUCKLES)

57:57.750 --> 58:00.667
Miljan wants to meet,
so as she is actually

58:00.750 --> 58:03.542
constructing her own plan
of how to take him down,

58:03.834 --> 58:06.417
he is constructing his plan
of how to take her down.

58:06.709 --> 58:09.583
And so it is
the ultimate Western showdown.

58:09.667 --> 58:12.458
And they both know that they are
very worthy adversaries.

58:12.542 --> 58:14.542
You better have thought this
all the way through.

58:14.750 --> 58:16.166
The situation with Miljan,

58:16.250 --> 58:17.792
who's been the puppet master
all along,

58:17.875 --> 58:20.458
it goes back to the same theme
of like, the men are the ones

58:20.542 --> 58:22.792
that are passionate and romantic
and Jett is the one

58:22.875 --> 58:25.166
that's practical
and logical the entire time.

58:25.250 --> 58:26.750
He threatened to kill Alice.

58:27.125 --> 58:30.625
Charlie refuses to be told
by Miljan what to do.

58:30.709 --> 58:33.291
Your son, Junior,
did this to you.

58:33.375 --> 58:35.917
But you were too blind
to see it.

58:36.000 --> 58:37.125
SEBASTIAN GUTIERREZ:
This is a show that...

58:37.208 --> 58:38.917
bad things happen,
people die.

58:39.417 --> 58:41.500
But in that very last moment,
it's important to me

58:41.583 --> 58:44.750
that he goes out with a sort
of honorable fashion.

58:45.709 --> 58:46.875
Two wild cards.

58:48.458 --> 58:49.375
(GUNSHOT)

58:49.458 --> 58:51.291
The fact that Charlie dies
because of her,

58:51.375 --> 58:53.542
she could have never foreseen
that it could have gotten

58:53.625 --> 58:54.583
to this place.

58:57.375 --> 58:59.041
Alice, run! Run!

58:59.792 --> 59:01.291
ALICE: (YELLING) Phoenix!

59:01.375 --> 59:02.417
(GRUNTS)

59:07.250 --> 59:08.125
(SOBS) He took her.

59:08.542 --> 59:10.417
CARLA GUGINO:
It's not until Miljan says

59:10.500 --> 59:13.875
that he has Alice
that it changes for her.

59:14.458 --> 59:16.208
Did you honestly think
that I would walk

59:16.291 --> 59:19.166
into a situation with you
without taking out insurance?

59:19.250 --> 59:21.458
The thing that really struck me
when I read it

59:21.542 --> 59:24.125
is that I thought there was
no way she would kill him

59:24.208 --> 59:25.208
because of Alice.

59:25.625 --> 59:26.917
-(GLASS BREAKS)
-(MILJAN GRUNTS)

59:27.000 --> 59:28.625
-Oh, God!
-(MILJAN SCREAMS)

59:28.709 --> 59:29.792
Where's my daughter?

59:29.959 --> 59:34.291
At every turn, Jett just does
not what a typical...

59:34.375 --> 59:35.291
not even typical,

59:35.375 --> 59:37.458
not what almost any mother
would do.

59:37.792 --> 59:40.041
She would rather take a chance
finding out the daughter

59:40.125 --> 59:43.125
on her own than still being
beholden to this guy.

59:43.208 --> 59:46.250
MILJAN: Victor Sulnic
will never forgive this.

59:46.917 --> 59:48.750
He will hunt you down
and kill you.

59:48.834 --> 59:50.000
I'll take my chances.

59:51.917 --> 59:54.583
The very end of the episode
is the first moment

59:54.667 --> 59:57.333
that she's hit by feelings
that she never knew

59:57.417 --> 59:58.709
she was capable of having.

59:59.000 --> 1:00:01.083
She didn't want
to feel this way,

1:00:01.166 --> 1:00:04.083
but that she might have been
part of her daughter

1:00:04.166 --> 1:00:07.166
for sure being in danger
and maybe not being alive.

1:00:08.041 --> 1:00:09.834
(BULLETS CLATTERING)

1:00:10.125 --> 1:00:12.500
GUTIERREZ: Jack Dillon
has completely gone off the edge

1:00:12.583 --> 1:00:14.959
after the murder
of his partner and lover,

1:00:15.041 --> 1:00:17.583
and at the moment
that he's at his lowest

1:00:17.667 --> 1:00:19.166
and is going to kill himself,

1:00:19.417 --> 1:00:21.709
Jett reveals
that he is Alice's father.

1:00:21.959 --> 1:00:23.625
I'm sorry
I didn't tell you before.

1:00:23.709 --> 1:00:25.583
GUTIERREZ: And I don't
necessarily need it to be

1:00:25.667 --> 1:00:28.083
like a big reveal
and more of an inevitable one.

1:00:28.166 --> 1:00:30.000
It's like there's a reason
why she goes to him.

1:00:30.083 --> 1:00:32.959
There's a reason why these two
have had a connection.

1:00:33.166 --> 1:00:35.208
(VOICE BREAKING)
I don't know if she's alive.

1:00:38.208 --> 1:00:39.208
I'll help you find her.

1:00:39.583 --> 1:00:42.458
If the first season was about
setting up all these characters

1:00:42.542 --> 1:00:44.792
and all these pieces
on the board and going forward,

1:00:44.875 --> 1:00:47.834
these characters will figure out
how to get back up again,

1:00:47.917 --> 1:00:50.166
but it is scary
what's happening to them

1:00:50.375 --> 1:00:52.667
and hopefully
people will feel that

1:00:52.750 --> 1:00:54.291
and feel for them and wonder

1:00:54.375 --> 1:00:56.333
how they're going to get out
of this situation.

1:00:56.417 --> 1:00:58.000
♪ (MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

1:00:58.542 --> 1:00:59.667
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
